# Database overview (MySQL via Prisma)

Amounts use Decimal columns (usually Decimal(19,2)). Time fields are DateTime. Sensitive fields are annotated for prisma-field-encryption with comments like /// @encrypted and @encryption:hash(...).

Core entities
- Account — tenant/root container for budgets, registers, categories, etc.
- User — login identity with role (USER/ADMIN), country/timezone preferences; email/password encrypted; jwtKey for token rotation
- Budget — groups registers and reporting within an account (default/archived flags)
- AccountRegister — an individual register (checking/savings/credit/loan/asset/cash/crypto). Contains balance/limits/APRs/loan params and integration fields (Plaid, crypto wallet, depreciation, categories), plus collateral/parent relations and sort orders
- RegisterEntry — ledger entries attached to a register; supports reconciliation, Plaid linkage, categorization, manual/projected flags, typeId
- RegisterEntryType — catalog for entry typing
- Interval — generic interval catalog (used for statement cycles and reoccurrence schedules/adjustments)

Recurring and scheduling
- Reoccurrence — recurring transaction definition with schedule (interval+count), optional transfer target, amount adjustments (mode/direction/value/interval), category, and generated entries
- ReoccurrenceSplit — break a recurrence into multiple target registers with fixed or percent amounts
- ReoccurrenceSkip — explicit skip markers by account/register/date
- ReoccurrencePlaidNameAlias — normalized name aliases for matching Plaid transactions to recurrences

Billing and reminders
- BillProfile — wraps a recurrence to add bill semantics (payee, grace days, reminders, expected ranges)
- BillInstance — concrete dated bill with amount, status lifecycle, and optional linkage to a paid register entry

Reconciliation and snapshots
- ReconciliationPeriod — statement window with opening/ending balances, status, ledger cleared balance, difference; links to a closing adjustment entry
- ReconciliationItem — per-entry clearance tracking during a period
- AccountSnapshot — saved point-in-time snapshot at account level
- AccountRegisterSnapshot + RegisterEntrySnapshot — snapshot rows for registers and entries
- AccountRegisterSummary — monthly summary by register (balance, month/year)

Categories and reporting
- Category — hierarchical (parent via subCategoryId), scoped optionally to account; linked to entries/recurrences and may provide default payment/interest categories for registers
- NotificationEvent / NotificationDismissal — tracking and suppression for in-app notifications (FORECAST_RISK, REOCCURRENCE_HEALTH)
- Reports: Implemented at service layer (e.g., reports/CategoryReportService) rather than as schema tables

Integrations and logs
- PlaidItem — linkage from user to Plaid item (no access token here)
- PlaidSyncCursor — per-item cursor for incremental Plaid sync
- PlaidSyncLog — structured log of sync runs (mode, status, timing, counts, errors)
- IntegrationAlert — structured alerts for integration failures/errors
- IntegrationJobLog — job-centric log entries

Security and keys
- Rsa — persisted RSA keypairs with isDefault/isArchived
- OpenAiRequestLog — OpenAI API usage logging including tokens/ids/status

Cash and crypto (recent additions)
- CashOnHand — banknote denomination counts for a register (ones/fives/tens/etc.)
- EvmChain — chain metadata (name, networkId, symbol, explorer, isDefault)
- CryptoRegisterChain — linkage between a register and enabled EVM chains
- CryptoTokenBalance — token snapshot per register/network/token; includes displayBalance, priceUsd, valueUsd, logoUrl, syncedAt

Access and invites
- UserAccount — membership on accounts with fine-grained permissions and allowedBudgetIds/allowedAccountRegisterIds
- AccountInvite — invite sent by a user to an email with expiry and tokenHash; AccountInviteAccount maps invited permissions to specific accounts

Indexes and constraints (selected)
- Many @index and @unique directives across foreign keys and natural keys
- Functional uniqueness noted (categories per account and parent) is enforced via SQL migration not expressible in Prisma schema

Encryption flags (examples)
- User.email, User.password — /// @encrypted (with emailHash as @encryption:hash(email))
- AccountRegister.name, plaidId/plaidAccessToken, walletAddress — encrypted/hashed variants
- RegisterEntry.description, plaidId — encrypted/hashed variants
- Reoccurrence.description — encrypted

Microservice schema
- microservice/prisma/schema.prisma mirrors a necessary subset of models (accounts, users, registers, entries, categories, recurrences, intervals, RSA, OpenAI log, etc.) to support maintenance operations and encryption rotation.
